        "type": "compound",
        "label": "Milvus access token (`username:password` or Zilliz Cloud API key)",
        "setup": "For self-hosted Milvus with authentication enabled, use the username and password configured for your Milvus instance and concatenate them as `username:password` (for example `root:milvus`) before sending as a bearer token. The REST API docs describe this directly in [Get Started](https://milvus.io/api-reference/restful/v3.0.x/About.md). For Milvus CLI, pass the same value with `connect -t` or set `ZILLIZ_TOKEN` as shown in [Milvus_CLI Command Reference](https://milvus.io/docs/cli_commands.md). If you are using Zilliz Cloud instead of self-hosted Milvus, the CLI docs state `-t` also accepts a Zilliz Cloud API key in [Milvus_CLI Command Reference](https://milvus.io/docs/cli_commands.md).",
